---
description: Keep responses short; act on minor process decisions silently
alwaysApply: true
---

# Be brief

- Default to short answers. No long recaps, no multi-section summaries
  unless asked.
- For minor process/release choices (tagging, version bumps, branch vs
  direct commit, changelog wording, commit splitting), just pick a
  sensible option and do it. Don't explain or offer it as a question.
- Do NOT create release tags unless explicitly asked.
- Skip "here's what I did and why" play-by-play for routine work; a
  one-line result is enough.
